gomodel:SYNGO_752  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In figure 6 the authors demonstrate that synaptojanin 2 is present in presynaptic nerve terminals. I find no information to support a functional role for synaptojanin 2 in the synapse. I am uncertain if this protein should be included in the annotation effort.. Experimental description: From legend to figure 6, \"Double immunofluorescence micrographs of rat brain sections stained with a rabbit polyclonal antibody for synaptojanin 2B...\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
